refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
boolopenssl_csr_export OpenSSLCertificateSigningRequeststringcsr stringoutput boolno_text&true;
openssl_csr_export takes the Certificate Signing Request represented by csr and stores it in PEM format in output, which is passed by reference.

&reftitle.parameters;



   &openssl.param.csr;

   output



     on success, this string will contain the PEM
     encoded CSR




   no_text

    &note.openssl.param-notext;

&reftitle.changelog;





    &Version;
    &Description;





    8.0.0

     csr accepts an OpenSSLCertificateSigningRequest instance now;
     previously, a &resource; of type OpenSSL X.509 CSR was accepted.

  &reftitle.examples;



    openssl_csr_export() example


<?php
$subject = array(
    "commonName" => "example.com",
);
$private_key = openssl_pkey_new(array(
    "private_key_bits" => 2048,
    "private_key_type" => OPENSSL_KEYTYPE_RSA,
));
$configargs = array(
    'digest_alg' => 'sha256WithRSAEncryption'
);
$csr = openssl_csr_new($subject, $private_key, $configargs);
openssl_csr_export($csr, $csr_string);
echo $csr_string;
?>
